When Oracle won't activate a new employee or re-activate a repeat hire that is returning more than year from last employed anymore than 60 days prior to the contract start date, we CANNOT use a Middlebury email to send them visa documentation they need in time for them to apply for a visa and get here.  It is the recommendation of ITS for security protocols we only use Midd emails for this purpose but we CANNOT and it's ridiculous.  And that's just ONE thing we struggle with.  If we had a decent CRM we could upload the docs in that system and provide the individuals secure access to that system to get the docs they need. It's disgusting for an institution of Middlebury's caliber and for the high percentage of international faculty/staff/students we work with annually that we don't have something like that already.
